Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 350
degrees. Peel @Yukon Gold Potatoes{16%ounce}, then cut into ½-inch cubes. Place in a
#medium pot{} with a pinch of @salt{} and enough water to cover by 1 inch. Bring
to a boil and cook until easily pierced by a knife, about ~{12%minutes}. Drain,
then return to #pot.

Spread out @Hazelnuts{1%ounce} on a #baking sheet{}. Toast in oven until golden
brown, ~{5-8%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate to cool, then roughly chop.

> Keep an eye on them—they can burn easily.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and mince @Shallot{1}(minced) until you have 2 TBSP. Halve
@Heirloom Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Mince @Chives{1/4%ounce} until you have ¼ cup.
Cut @Meyer Lemon{1} into wedges. After returning potatoes to pot, mash with a
#potato masher{} or #fork. Stir in @Milk{1/2%cup}. Season with salt and pepper.

> Add more milk, if needed, to achieve a creamy consistency.

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pan{} over
medium-high heat. Pat @Scallops{8%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}, then season
all over with salt and @pepper{}. Add to pan and cook until browned and just
firm, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside, covered, to keep
warm.

Reduce heat under pan to medium. Add a drizzle of oil and @Butter{1%tablespoon} and
allow butter to melt. Add minced shallot and tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook, tossing, until shallot is translucent and tomato is softened, ~{3-5%minutes}.
Stir in @White Wine Vinegar{1%tablespoon} and half the minced chives. Cook until
chives have just started to wilt, about ~{30%seconds} more. Remove pan from heat.

Divide mashed potatoes between plates. Top with scallops, then spoon shallot and
tomato mixture over top. Sprinkle with hazelnuts and remaining minced chives.
Serve with lemon wedges on the side for squeezing over.